  "texts": [
    "Protected classes include: • Age • Race • Sex • Religion or belief • Sexual orientation • Disability GDPR To prevent algorithmic discrimination, Art.",
    "22 notes that where data processing could impact persons in a legal or similarly significant manner and, in particular, give rise to discrimination, persons may object to solely automated decisionmaking, for example, decisions made solely by an AI system (see Baldini, 2019; ICO, 2023).",
    "Further regulation may apply within certain jurisdictions regarding the treatment of policyholders, such as the Insurance Act (2015) in the UK or Colorado's (2021) SB21-169, in the US, which restricts the insurers' use of external consumer data concerning protecting consumers from unfair discrimination.In addition, global standards currently under development such as ISO/IEC FDIS 420019 (ISO and IEC, 2023) may apply, which focusses on how to manage AI systems, including governance and trust.",
    "Key themes in ISO/IEC 42001 includes fairness, transparency, explainability, accountability, reliability, privacy, and security (Levene, 2023).",
    "Actuarial professional guidance."
  ]
}